    "steps": [
        {
            "step": "Cut Chicken Thighs into 1 inch pieces. Add to a bowl and mix with Salt, Garlic Powder, White Pepper, Wine, and Egg. Refrigerate for 20-30 minutes. Add Corcn Starch and mix until it disappears. Add Oil and mix until the oil is not visible"
        },
        {
            "step": "Mix Sugar, Vinegar, and Chili Garlic Sauce in a bowl. Mix in Brown Sauce"
        },
        {
            "step": "Deep Fry Chicken at 350F until golden brown. Let chicken drain off excess oil on a wire rack"
        },
        {
            "step": "Create a Corn Starch Slurry by mixing 1 tbsp of Corn Starch and 2 tbsp of Water in a small bowl. Add Chicken and General Tso's Sauce to a pan over high heat. Coat Chicken in General Tso's Sauce. Stir in Corn Starch Slurry and mix until sauce thickens"
        }
    ]
}